Description:

History: The term 'micromosaic' was given to this type of jewelry in reference to the Roman mosaics that were famously made of tesserae, or little glass bricks. Product name: Antique Imari Plate
Description:
This listing is for an antique Imari-ware plate made about 120-130 years ago.  It is hand-painted and the overglaze is slightly raised, thus giving the plate a slight texture when you run your finger over it.  It is decorated with cranes, matsu pine and blossoms, and it has a Kinrande textile pattern. 
 
Kinrande refers to extravagantly decorated gold painted porcelain.  Patterns include cobalt blue underglaze with red and gold overglazes.  Originally Kinrande porcelain was produced for export, as the domestic market preferred more simple porcelain-ware.  Fine tableware and high-shouldered jars with gold brocade designs began to enjoy popularity in Japan by the end of the late Edo period after a decline in the first half of the 18th century.  
Imari-ware refers to pottery produced in Okawachiyama Village in Imari town. It is roughly divided into four different types: Iro-Nabeshima, Nabeshima-Sometsuke, Nabeshima-Seiji, and Nabeshima/Koimari. Iro-Nabeshima is characterized by red, yellow and green designs painted on a pure white or blue and white background. Nabeshima-Sometsuke uses indigo blue paint on a white base, Nabeshima-Seiji is pale green or blue-green coloured pottery, and Nabeshima/Koimari is the name given to porcelain produced in the kilns of the Nabeshima clan. Koimari refers to porcelain produced during the Edo and Meiji Periods.

Product name: Antique French silk collapsible top hat Gibus black opera steampunk top hat antique victorian mens top hat w gilded stamps and monogram C
Description:
Rare antique French black silk top hat gibus with a gilded stamp 
Late 1800s 
This collapsible hat (called chapeau claque in France) is held open by springs and with a gentle push, folds flat to be stored 
The hat is of a shiny black silk, which feels very soft and tactile
The hat is fully lined in black silk with a gilded stamp representing a shield with a lion, unicorn, with a crown and a C monogram
It reads "chapellerie nouvelle HUC famille" with the adress of the shopmaker in Pezenas
The borders of the hat are well curved
This hat is in a good vintage condition with some wear to the lining and rim, this does not detract from the beauty of this rare tophat
Please see pictures for the details
The opening system still works well with the springs
Sizes of the opera hat: 6 inches high (15cm), approx. 21.2 inches around the interior band (53cm)
Great for display and also still ready for use 
A highly collectible piece, as these collapsible top hats are getting very rare, especially in such a good condition
Perfect for the Victorian Steampunk clothing addict and the Gothic clothing lover
Much prettier in reality than on the pictures, believe me
I have more mens hats in my Etsy shop, top hats and bowler hats, please take a look

Product name: 36" Large Rustic Wall Clock
Description:
This Large Rustic Clock is a great addition to any home decor. The clock has been handmade using rough cut lumber from some back wood mills near the foothills of the Adirondacks. Each clock is hand crafted and finished using a distressing technique that gives it a reclaimed, barn wood look. 
This clock has an approximate diameter of 36" and the clock face is about 1" from the wall when hung.  It has a quiet high torque clock mechanism / movement. It does come in three pieces and requires some light assembly. I am guessing under 10 min for most people. All you need is a phillips screw driver or screw gun. Doing this saves a bunch of money on shipping. 
This is a stock photo, the actual clock will be slightly different due to the sanding and grain patterns of the wood. The hands will be those in the image with the white background. We had too many issues with the hands with the open ends as they were cheaper hands and were not balanced correctly. 
I have many other round and square clocks in my Etsy store ranging from 18" to 42".  Clocks can be personalized as well.  If you have any questions please ask.
If you wish to personalize the clock please choose the personalization option and put what you want it to say in the note to seller section. Note personalized clocks are non-refundable.

Description:
Intensive therapy cream 
This cream is amazing.  A pea size lasts all day with fabulous results.
The ingredients in my products are pure without fillers or being water downed.   Most in the market lotions have a high water intake.  My products contain ingredients in their pure raw form.  This product was, for me, a life saver.  All of the ingredients have been chosen to eliminate the scales of lesions as well as moisturizing them as well.  I was shocked at how well this product worked.
My latest reviews:
                                      "Both my son and I suffer from psoriasis. We have been using this cream for about a week and it is really making a difference in the thickness and scaliness of our skin. Thanks."
 
                                       "Psoriasis Eczema Intensive Therapy Skin Cream - Burdock Root"
5 out of 5 stars     
Amazing product. Thank you so much!
This large 4 ounce jar will last a long time due to the rich nature of the product.
The photos depicted is my experience with this cream for a particularly psoriatic lesion.  With twice daily application of this cream, this lesion healed and disappeared.
I use this product on my at risk areas each morning after a shower while my skin is still damp and again at night before I go to bed.  This cream is so rich, that each area should only require a pea size application.  While it may feel a bit greasy at first, the rich plant oils and plant butters absorb quickly providing you with lasting hydration and protection.   The photos are my actual lesions before and after.
I know the challenges of psoriasis.  Having suffered with psoriasis and psoriatic arthritis for decades, the disease was illusive to any non-prescription products.  After enduring round after round of chemo, and, the unfortunate side affects of the drugs, I knew that I had to develop suitable cleansing and skin care products.  I have made an all-natural intensive skin therapy cream for years which has been vital to reducing my flare ups as well as those suffered by many of my customers.  Most moisturizing soaps and creams for psoriasis and eczema contained tar, artificial fragrances and filler that actually worsened my condition.  I could not tolerate shampoos made with tar or that contained artificial fragrances.  
The search for natural remedies was extensive until I developed a combination of known herbal remedies.    This product was created to help eliminate the scales, sores, inflammation and itching associated with skin lesions associated with psoriasis and eczema. My skin became involved to the point that it  I was embarrassed.  I began using this product 2x per day and on a morning and nightly basis.  My lesions have reduced by about 90% and those did not clear within 2 weeks reduced in size.   It has been a Godsend for me.  I have been making this product for years and people rave about the changes they made in their skin.
This listing is for a large 4 oz jar.   It takes only a pea size amount of product for a local area.  This cream is very dense and each jar should last for several months at the recommended usage. Deep rich natural emollients with wonderful exfoliating ingredients to penetrate the build up and scales of the diseases.
This dense quality cream includes burdock root, aloe vera, soy, olive and jojoba oils, shea butter, bees wax, honey, cocoanut oil, aloe Vera, honey, witch hazel and essential oils which hydrate, soften and reduce the scaling lesions of psoriasis and eczema as well as a propriety combination of natural plant extracts and emollients.   It does not include any animal byproducts or petroleum products.
Please see my youtube.com video for additional information.  User:  Marrs Mercantile relating to application and benefits of this skin care product.

**I've recently launched a new website that has my newest and best interactive hand lettering learning outlets! eCourses on finding & developing your own style, Etsy & Instagram for your lettering, Inspired Lettering and more. All my courses come with printable workbooks!

Hi there!
My "Begintermediate" Guide to Hand Lettering Workbook got a whole new face lift! I am so excited about it.
Hand Lettering is everywhere these days! It adds an organic flair to just about anything from wedding envelopes to your kids student council poster ;)
I've taught hundreds of people to learn the art of hand lettering, and you can totally learn too!
This workbook and guide is all my hard earned tips, tricks, letter drills, and examples to help guide you, teach you, and inspire you!
You may have dabbled in some sort of calligrahy before, or never picked up a brush pen in your life. This workbook is great for levels varying from just starting out, to an early intermediate letterer. It's hard to put each person in a beginner OR intermediate group... which is how "Begintermediate" was born! Those lines are blurry, and now there's a guide to take you from the beginning, pushing you to create beautiful letter forms AND awesome letter connections and an early intermediate level! :) 
Included in the workbook:
hand lettering terms and rules
warm up practice drills and why we do them
my simple hand lettering style of alphabet with specific instruction on how to draw each letter
practice drills to help you master your new pen, and my style of lettering
intro to letter connections
letter connection practice drill
intro to composition and how to improve yours!
The book is printed on high quality super smooth 70lb paper, and spiral bound.
Tracing paper is included in your kit to help extend the life of your workbook, and to give you some "instant gratification" when learning hand lettering. (Trace over my letters!)
NOW for a LIMITED TIME each Kit comes with one of my new soon-to-be-released 2017 PRINTS!

Product name: Glamorous Gold Metallic Edible Paint by Sweet Sticks
Description:
Just SHAKE, POUR & PAINT! 
NOT RECOMMENDED FOR CHOCOLATE OR CHOCOLATE COATED CAKE POPS!
Edible Art 'Metallics' Decorative Paint by Sweet Sticks is a range of revolutionary paints made in Australia. With a unique blend of 100% edible ingredients they can paint, dry and be rub free on many surfaces making cake decorating quicker, easier and more effective. 
Our paints take away the need to mix lustre and alcohol together that makes one big mess most of the time and money. Simply shake, pour & paint. 
- Fondant
- Buttercream cakes (chilled)
- Sugar cookies
- Marshmallows
- Confectionary
- Ganache
- Modelling chocolate
- Macarons
- Fruit ie: Berries
Our edible metallic paints can be applied a number of ways but we recommend good quality brushes (sable brushes work amazingly) and long brush strokes. 
The paint is ready to use from the bottle, so there is no need to thin it out or mix it with any other ingredients. Once applied and dried the pigment is sealed within the surface - no dust or smudges! 
Shake well before and during use. 
Keep away from children and store in a dry cool place. 
Bottle is 15ml.
GETTING STARTED TIPS & TRICKS 
SHAKE, SHAKE, SHAKE!
There's a whole lot of lustre in that bottle!
If paint is transparent, keep shaking
If you need to add more paint to your palette, shake beforehand
Brushes are important, take the time and find a brush that suits you and the paint
Long brush strokes show amazing results
We find lying the bottles flat in between use allows the lustre to blend quicker
Our paint dries rub free so it's worth the wait in dry time. No more white gloves!
If these paints are new to you, take the time and have a play. Don't compare them to other products on the market because there isn't anything like it. Have fun with them.

Paints on fondant
Paints on chilled buttercream
Paints on macarons
Paints on heaps of other things too! Dries in one hour or less
It√¢‚Ç¨‚Ñ¢s actually rub free! No fuss!

100% food grade edible
Gluten, dairy, soy and peanut free! A little bottle goes a long way

Plastic bags are wonderful for protecting jewelry pieces. *Jewelry should only be put on after washing and applying any makeup, hair spray, gels, lotions or perfume. *Try to protect any jewelry from harsh chemicals, extreme temperatures and sunlight. *Always try to store your beaded necklaces or bracelets flat. *You should not wear beaded jewelry while doing household or outdoor chores. *You should never wear any jewelry when swimming or showering. The chlorine can cause damage. Please do not swim or shower with your beads. *Wipe with a damp cloth and if need be a little mild dish soap, but do not immerse. *Store your jewelry in a clean, dry place. *Jewelry should never be dipped or used in an ultrasonic cleaner. *Avoid dropping and hard contact (i.e., knocking against objects). *Put on jewelry last when dressing and take off first when undressing.
